Gallery : The maternal gallery is constructed near or below the root collar, upward from the entrance hole, longitudinal and slightly sinuate from 60–120 mm long (
Schwerdtfeger 1957
). The larval tunnels extend from both sides of the maternal gallery (
Wood 1982
).

Distribution (
Fig. 21
). CENTRAL AMERICA : Honduras , Guatemala and El Salvador ; NORTH AMERICA : Arizona and New Mexico to southern Mexico .
